<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000006#     2#         1122#">Va. Code Ann. § 6.2-1122</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_6.2-1122"/><heading><desig>§ 6.2-1122.</desig><title>Meetings of board of directors</title></heading><bodyText><p>The board of directors of every state savings institution shall hold meetings at least once in every calendar month. At any meeting a majority of the whole board shall be necessary for the lawful transaction of business, unless the stockholders or members, by bylaw, have fixed another number, which in the case of a state savings bank shall be not less than five, as a quorum. The Commission may allow less frequent meetings, but not less often than quarterly.</p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>Code 1950, § 6-201.35; 1960, c. 402; 1966, c. 584, § 6.1-165; 1972, c. 796, § 6.1-195.42; 1985, c. 425, § 6.1-194.15; <citation normalizedCite="1991 VA CH 230"><content><span normalizedCite="1991 Va. Ch. 230">1991, c. 230<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1991#000230#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, § 6.1-194.118; <citation normalizedCite="2010 VA CH 794"><content><span normalizedCite="2010 Va. Ch. 794">2010, c. 794<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2010#000794#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGr